## 8. Verification — End-to-End Test



Against `experiments/baseline/dummy-infra/` (75 null_resources across 6 modules):



### Gate enforcement

1. Start server with `TERRAFORM_MCP_GATE=read` (default)

2. Verify: apply, destroy, import, state_rm, state_mv are NOT listed

3. Start server with `TERRAFORM_MCP_GATE=write`

4. Verify: apply, import, state_mv visible; destroy, state_rm still hidden

5. Start server with `TERRAFORM_MCP_GATE=destroy`

6. Verify: all 17 tools visible



### CLI tools

7. Call `terraform_init` → success

8. Call `terraform_plan` → shows 75 resources

9. Call `terraform_apply` (gate=write) with `confirm: true` → 75 resources created



### GraphQL + schema context

10. Call `get_schema()` → see full SDL + prebuilt queries with real resource IDs

11. Call `get_schema(module: "networking")` → see networking-focused prebuilt queries

12. Call `get_schema(resource: "module.networking.null_resource.vpc")` → see VPC-centered queries

13. Copy a prebuilt query → call `query_graph` → get real data

14. Call `query_graph` with impact query → see cascade analysis

15. Call `query_graph` with path query → see dependency chain



### State hash detection

16. Run `terraform apply` in a SEPARATE terminal (outside MCP)

17. Call `query_graph` → DAG auto-detects stale state, rebuilds from fresh `.tfstate`



### DAG rebuild on apply

18. Call `terraform_destroy` with `confirm: true` (gate=destroy) → DAG invalidated

19. Call `query_graph` again → DAG rebuilds from fresh state

